    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Is property styling worth the money when selling in Brisbane?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "For most Brisbane inner east properties in the $700,000 to $2,000,000 range, professional styling returns between two and four times its cost in price premium, provided the property, location, and buyer pool are right. Vacant properties, properties with dated interiors, and prestige homes benefit most. Well-presented occupied homes with good existing furniture often do not need a full styling engagement."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What return on investment can I expect from property styling in Brisbane?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "A styling spend of $3,000 to $5,000 on a well-located Brisbane inner east home typically produces a price premium of $8,000 to $20,000, driven primarily by higher enquiry volume and stronger open home attendance. The ROI is highest for vacant properties and for properties where the buyer pool is broad owner-occupier, not investor-focused."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "When should I not spend money on property styling in Brisbane?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Styling is not the right investment for properties targeting an investor or developer buyer pool, where decisions are based on yield and land value rather than presentation. It is also less valuable for properties in strong markets where genuine scarcity is driving demand regardless of presentation quality. Ask your agent whether buyer competition in your suburb is currently driven by presentation or by raw demand."
      }
    }
  ]
